    "response_text": "The commercial unfolds in a brightly lit store aisle, apparently a personal-care or toiletries section, with shelves full of bottles and cans.\n\nAt the start, a young man in a green jacket stands in the aisle while a young woman with long dark hair walks away carrying a green shopping basket. The man looks toward the shelves, which are stocked with many products. The camera then moves closer to him as he faces a shelf of body-spray/deodorant-type products.\n\nA close-up shows rows of black cans labeled “TAG.” A hand reaches in and removes one can from the shelf. Behind the cans, a blonde woman’s face is visible out of focus, looking through or past the shelf. The man is then shown holding the black TAG can and looking at it.\n\nThe next shots emphasize women noticing him. A close-up shows the blonde woman’s face, framed between shelf gaps, staring forward. The man continues examining the can. Another shot shows the blonde woman, wearing a red top, pressed close to the shelf from the opposite side. The man raises his hand or the product near his neck/chest area. A brunette woman in a white top looks sideways with a focused expression.\n\nThe scene then turns chaotic. The man reaches toward the shelf and products begin to fall or scatter. In a wide aisle shot, many small black cans are on the floor around him. He reacts with surprise, turning toward the store’s checkout area. A woman with long dark hair in a white top runs directly toward him; her hair is blown back by the motion. She tackles or grabs him from behind/above, and both drop low near the shelves.\n\nThe action becomes a fast, slapstick chase-and-pileup sequence. The woman in white slides forward across the floor as the man crouches or stumbles. In the wider store area, more women rush in from different directions. The man jumps or is knocked upward while women converge around him. A blonde woman in a pink top and other women collide with him; bodies tumble and slide across the floor. Cans remain scattered across the aisle. Another woman in a green sleeveless top runs in, and the group ends up in a pile on the floor, with the man surrounded by several women.\n\nA full-screen warning card appears on a darkened background. Large red text reads “WARNING.” Smaller white text says: “The makers of TAG body spray accept no responsibility for any injuries resultant from the wearing of this product. Any getting down and/or funky, however, you can totally blame on us. We’re good like that.” There is also a line of fine print at the bottom that is partially visible.\n\nAfter the warning, there is a close-up of the man lying in the middle of several women’s faces and bodies, looking up at them. The final product shot shows a single black TAG body-spray can centered against a black background. In the last frame, text appears beside it: “CONSIDER YOURSELF WARNED,” with “WARNED” in red."
